## CRITICAL ARCHITECTURE RULES

### 1. Zero Overhead / Ancient High-Tech
NEVER store redundant data. Every byte must earn its place.
- Word positions encoded via template codes (1-2 bytes), NOT raw position arrays
- Tier markers are WASTE - tier is inferred from byte-length
- Format: [word_symbol][vertical_code][horizontal_code] = 3 bytes minimum

### 2. Encoding Tiers (Tier-Marker-FREE)
```
Tier 0A: 1 byte  → single ultra-common positions (codes 0x00-0x0F)
Tier 0B: 1 byte  → common 1-2 position patterns (94 templates)
Tier 1:  2 bytes → 3-position patterns (8,836 templates)
Tier 2:  variable → 0xFF + delta encoding (unlimited, any pattern)

Decoder infers tier from byte-length. NO separate tier marker bytes!
```

### 3. Template System
8,946 pre-computed templates covering ~95% of real-world position patterns.
- Tier 0A: 16 templates (single positions on key lines)
- Tier 0B: 94 templates (1-2 position patterns)
- Tier 1: 8,836 templates (3-position patterns)
- Tier 2: delta fallback for anything not in templates

### 4. Import Policy (HARDCODED HIGHWAYS)
Always import from exact production module names:
```python
from production_scanner import EnhancedCleanWordToVisualSymbolScannerWithMicroscopicLines
from SIMPLE_WORD_SYMBOL_MAPPING_SYSTEM import SimpleWordSymbolMapping
```
NO abstraction layers. Direct imports are intentional.

### 5. Dictionary Architecture
Oxford 250K master dictionary and NEW_WORDS_DISCOVERED.json are PERMANENT.
Never truncate, purge, or "clean up" dictionary data.

### 6. Military-Grade Overhead Protection
MilitaryGradeOverheadEnforcer BLOCKS multi-byte symbols and overhead data.
This is SECURITY SUCCESS, not a bug. Never work around it.

## What NOT to Touch

- `archives/`, `fortressv*/`, `FORTRESS_V*/` - Historical versions, ignore
- `CONSOLIDATED_STRATEGIC_BACKUPS/` - Backups, ignore
- Files in root with dates in names (e.g., `*_20250721_*.py`) - Old backups
- `attached_assets/` - Replit-managed, ignore
- Any `.zip` files - Old snapshots

## Super Symbol Types
```
TYPE 1: Morphological variants (walk/walked/walking → one base symbol)
TYPE 2: Word forms (different POS of same word)
TYPE 3: Fixed sentences (common 3-4 word phrases)
TYPE 4: Contractions (can't, won't, etc. → 36 types)
```

## Grid Dimensions
- Document grid: 100 lines × 80 characters per line
- Vertical templates: which lines (1-100) a word appears on
- Horizontal templates: which position (1-80) within a line

## Hive Blockchain Context
- Target: 5KB Custom JSON per block
- Symbol stream: word_symbol + vertical_code + horizontal_code per word
- Templates stored client-side (never transmitted)
- Reconstruction: 100% deterministic from codes + templates
